---
title: Balsamic Fig Beef Tenderloin plus Honey Walnut Crostini, Brussels Sprouts & Parm Mashed Potatoes
description: Whether you’re cooking for one or the whole gang, this two-course stunner will help take the stress out of dinner–and add some luxury to your evening meal. You’ll start with a savory crostini appetizer topped with whipped ricotta, honey, and walnuts. And for the main, fig jam is paired with balsamic vinegar to create a tangy pan sauce to drizzle over tender beef tenderloin. Garlicky mashed potatoes and caramelized Brussels sprouts are the perfect accompaniments for this dinner designed for those of us who enjoy the finer things (and foods!) in life.
